  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers just broke above the massive -8844.9M negative gamma wall at 6500 with spot at 6522.85, triggering the 397-633% GEX surge as they were forced to buy futures aggressively to hedge short gamma positions. Now sitting in PIN regime below the 6553 flip strike, dealers are long gamma and will sell any rallies toward the 6545-6550 resistance cluster (4.6-4.8B positive gamma) while providing support on dips back toward 6525. Watch for mean reversion between 6525-6545 unless we break above 6553 flip strike, which would shift dealers to short gamma and accelerate any move toward 6600+.",
